%S A085244 1,3,14,112,872,14372,154480,3098480,59710816,1688186176,27925409152,
%T A085244 1327833590272,25675495200768,1017195720916224,47444016840290304,
%U A085244 2267031138313024512,56480432945454004224,4051971981329937580032
%N A085244 Permanent of the symmetric n X n matrix M defined by M(i,j) = gcd(i,j) for 1 <= i,j <= n.
%C A085244 From _Vico Bonfioli_, Jul 19 2026: (Start)
%C A085244 A prime p divides a(n) as soon as at least p integers in [1,n] have all their prime factors congruent to 1 mod p; in particular 2 | a(n) for n >= 3 and 3 | a(n) for n >= 13. The power of 2 can be sharpened: 4 | a(n) for n >= 4 and 8 | a(n) for n >= 17. These divisibility statements are machine-checked in Lean 4 (see link).
%C A085244 The 2-adic valuation v_2(a(n)) tends to infinity.
%C A085244 (a(n)/n!)^(1/n) tends to infinity: writing (a(n)/n!)^(1/n) = (log(n))^(theta+o(1)), one has 2*log(phi) - phi^(-2) <= theta <= log(2), where phi is the golden ratio (numerically theta is about 0.68). (End)
%H A085244 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="/A085244/b085244.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..38</a> (terms 1..23 from Herman Jamke).
%H A085244 Vico Bonfioli, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.21433867">Notes on gcd-matrix permanents, random cycle lifts, and d-matching polynomials, with Lean 4 formalizations</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%t A085244 A085244[n_] := Permanent[Array[GCD, {n, n}]];
%t A085244 Array[A085244, 15] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Dec 31 2025 *)
%o A085244 (PARI) permRWNb(a)=n=matsize(a)[1];if(n==1,return(a[1,1]));sg=1;in=vectorv(n);x=in;x=a[,n]-sum(j=1,n,a[,j])/2;p=prod(i=1,n,x[i]);for(k=1,2^(n-1)-1,sg=-sg;j=valuation(k,2)+1;z=1-2*in[j];in[j]+=z;x+=z*a[,j];p+=prod(i=1,n,x[i],sg));return(2*(2*(n%2)-1)*p)
%o A085244 for(n=1,26,a=matrix(n,n,i,j,gcd(i,j));print1(permRWNb(a)", ")) \\ Herman Jamke (hermanjamke(AT)fastmail.fm), May 13 2007
%o A085244 (PARI) a085244(n) = matpermanent(matrix(n,n,i,j,gcd(i,j))) \\ _Hugo Pfoertner_, Dec 31 2025
